    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2011-10-13</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2011-10-31T14:09:17Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Transparency in Judgment Payments Act of 2011 - Requires the Secretary of the Treasury, not later than 30 days after the payment of a final judgment, award, or compromise settlement involving a federal agency, to publish electronically: (1) the agency responsible for the payment; (2) a citation to the law under which the claim was made; (3) the amount &nbsp;to be paid, including any interest and attorney fees; and (4) the court in which such claim was filed and the court case number. </p> <p>Requires each federal agency to submit annual reports to Congress describing: (1) any civil action filed or pending against such agency or an agency employee, and (2) any settlements entered by, or final judgments entered against,&nbsp;such agency&nbsp;or an agency employee.&nbsp;</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
